            <thetext>The ToggleButton in Basic,iOS and Android theming, is only able to show &quot;ON&quot; and &quot;OFF&quot; as boolean state value.

SHOULD:
ToggleButton should be able to display short custom text like &quot;I&quot;,&quot;O&quot;,&quot;Agree&quot;,&quot;Deny&quot;,&quot;true&quot;,&quot;false&quot;.
This improves usability (More detailed information for users, what happens, when toggling), and makes adapting to native theme easier. For example: iOS 5 shows I/0 as text, iOS 5 used &quot;ON/OFF&quot;.

Update of Mobile Showcase forms site, for demonstrating this feature.</thetext>
